replies.body:
{{champion:157}} 
Max E. 
You are pro now.

{{champion:267}} 

Use your ult prior to using your Q on someone, as your ult will slow them down so much AND knock them up briefly that it becomes much easier to land her Q, almost guaranteeing a kill for your team.

{{champion:43}} 

You are more tanky than you realize. When fighting against super mobile ADCs (like Kalista or Vayne) there are many instances where you can run up to them in the middle of their own minion wave, hit them with a W and an ulted E, and (hopefully) your own ADC will quickly approach (I find this tactic works best with a Lucian) and destroy that ADC in seconds with the enemy support usually not able to prevent you from killing the ADC fast enough.

{{champion:266}} 
If you bring ignite (I usually don't) at level 2 you can cheese an enemy if you get W level 1 and Q level 2. Switch to Blood Price and get the third strike ready. As soon as you hit level 2 (Make sure you're pushing the enemy so that you hit level 2 first) grab Q and go in on them and ignite them as soon as you land and their health bar will explode. Most enemies won't expect it. Just be sure you kill them or at least push them out if you do this or you wasted your ignite and you don't have your E which is very useful.

You can win almost any lane as Aatrox by simply focusing on poking them down and out-sustaining them. Play kinda like Nasus. Only fight when you know you have the advantage and focus very hard on farming. Get ganks from your jungler and get ahead and then no one can fight you. Aatrox plays a lot like Nasus. Just farm. He scales incredibly well with Attack Speed and Lifesteal so Botrk is almost always my first item on him followed by a defensive item (Spirit Visage if I'm ahead or against an AP, Sunfire or DMP if I'm even or behind against an AD.) Sometimes I will get Maw first or second if the situation calls for it.

{{champion:91}} 
Your E has 750 range and increases your damage to the enemy you blink to and slows them making your passive proc on them. Combined with flash you have a 1175 range blink. This is farther than any adc can auto attack you unless you get hit by a trap or a net from {{champion:51}}. Using flash ever so slightly before E can catch the enemy team off guard when you just instantly blink into them from a very long distance away and blow up a squishy real fast and chunk the rest of the team with your AoE abilities, although you probably will sacrifice your life to do so unless your team follows up VERY quickly.
